01:05.018 --> 01:06.283
Hi, there!

01:06.319 --> 01:10.253
I'm Claire Warren, and
I'm running for City Council.

01:10.289 --> 01:11.388
Hi, there. Hi.

01:11.424 --> 01:14.123
I'm Claire Warren, and
I'm running for City Council.

01:14.158 --> 01:15.124
I want...

01:15.159 --> 01:16.058
Have a nice day.

01:16.093 --> 01:18.828
Vote for my mom!
She'll give you 10 bucks.

01:18.863 --> 01:19.733
- Danny!
- Hi!

01:19.758 --> 01:20.586
Hi, there.

01:20.611 --> 01:22.544
I'm Claire Warren, and
I'm running for City Council.

01:22.638 --> 01:24.504
Might I have just a moment with you?

01:24.539 --> 01:25.739
<i>You don't suck at this.</i>

01:25.774 --> 01:26.673
I do. I kind of suck at this.

01:26.708 --> 01:28.388
- Honey, no.
- I do.

01:28.423 --> 01:30.408
Who am I to think
that somebody will actually vote

01:30.444 --> 01:33.661
for some lame, cupcake-baking,
stay-at-home mom.

01:33.686 --> 01:34.886
 Really!

01:34.969 --> 01:37.036
Yo, can I bail now? I'm out of flyers.

01:37.071 --> 01:38.312
Mother, he's buying you votes.

01:38.337 --> 01:39.482
Great! How many?

01:39.518 --> 01:41.674
Hello! It's called election fraud.

01:41.709 --> 01:43.842
Okay. Let's get some ice cream.

01:43.878 --> 01:45.277
I can't believe this.

01:45.312 --> 01:47.446
Democracy is so dead.

01:48.882 --> 01:50.915
Hey.

01:50.951 --> 01:52.917
Oh, wow.

01:52.953 --> 01:55.920
This is the best one yet, Chief.

01:55.956 --> 01:57.121
Where's the crew?

01:57.156 --> 01:59.691
There is no crew. It's a ghost ship.

02:00.727 --> 02:02.794
Want some ice cream?

02:02.829 --> 02:05.929
 You're getting heavy.

02:05.965 --> 02:07.698
All right. See you, guys!

02:07.733 --> 02:09.259
See you later. Watch Adam!

02:09.285 --> 02:10.460
Yeah.

02:10.485 --> 02:12.302
Danny. Danny, wait!

02:12.337 --> 02:13.937
We're supposed to stay with Adam!

02:13.973 --> 02:17.107
And how can I help you there, son?

02:17.142 --> 02:18.875
Help you with something?

02:22.013 --> 02:24.714
I need a ride.

02:30.822 --> 02:32.287
Have you seen Adam?

02:34.258 --> 02:35.055
Hey!

02:35.090 --> 02:36.019
I can't find Adam.

02:36.044 --> 02:37.935
I've looked everywhere. He's gone.

02:37.970 --> 02:40.729
Well, look again. Come on.

02:46.298 --> 02:47.443
Man: Adam!

02:47.478 --> 02:49.738
- Adam!

03:06.747 --> 03:09.393
 The two of you were
supposed to be watching him!

03:09.447 --> 03:11.114
He was fine. He was with Willa, and...

03:11.149 --> 03:12.718
No, but you never should
have left them alone!

03:12.753 --> 03:14.514
You're the oldest! You're in charge!

03:14.535 --> 03:16.069
Except when he's getting to
third base with some slut.

03:16.103 --> 03:18.986
Like you'd ever know what
that is, you freak of nature!

03:19.021 --> 03:19.905
Stop it.

03:19.940 --> 03:22.074
Turning on each other
won't help anyone...

03:22.109 --> 03:23.208
Definitely not Adam.

03:23.243 --> 03:26.144
The first few hours of a
missing-child case are critical,

03:26.180 --> 03:28.707
and if you spend them
screaming at each other

03:28.743 --> 03:30.468
instead of remember what he was wearing,

03:30.503 --> 03:31.816
what he was doing, or
who he was doing it with,

03:31.851 --> 03:33.517
you might as well bury
your kid right now.

03:35.755 --> 03:37.321
You're the officer they sent?

03:37.356 --> 03:38.723
She's just a little girl, John.

03:38.758 --> 03:40.825
I'm the little girl
who's gonna find your son.

03:48.634 --> 03:50.767
 Who do you need to see again?

03:50.802 --> 03:52.760
Office Meyer.

03:52.787 --> 03:55.287
Well, watch out, man. It's
big-time detective now.

03:55.322 --> 03:57.523
She'll eat you for that.

03:57.558 --> 03:58.724
Meyer!

03:58.759 --> 04:00.759
What, Tom? What?

04:05.331 --> 04:07.298
Can I, uh, help you with something?

04:07.333 --> 04:09.467
You Nina Meyer?

04:09.502 --> 04:12.603
Yeah. And who are you?

04:16.642 --> 04:17.909
I'm him.

04:30.847 --> 04:32.914
I promised the people of Red Pines

04:32.949 --> 04:35.250
a return to family
values, and I meant it.

04:35.285 --> 04:37.151
 But don't you think
that firing Deputy Conroy

04:37.186 --> 04:38.885
while the affair is
still just alleged...

04:38.921 --> 04:41.054
No, I don't tolerate lying, Frank.

04:41.090 --> 04:42.990
You can just ask my kids, okay?

04:43.025 --> 04:45.159
- So when's the governor announcement?

04:45.194 --> 04:46.994
No idea what you're talking about.

04:47.029 --> 04:48.729
<i>She's the
politician in the family.</i>

04:48.764 --> 04:49.930
When'd you become the shady one?

04:49.965 --> 04:53.000
A long time ago, Paul. I
can take one more question.

04:53.035 --> 04:55.901
- Uh, could you make it brief?
- [Cellphones chiming]

04:55.937 --> 04:57.370
Holy crap.

04:57.405 --> 04:58.605
Mayor Warren!

04:58.640 --> 05:00.273
Have you spoken to the police
about the reappearance of Adam?

05:00.308 --> 05:01.541
Mother!

05:01.576 --> 05:02.642
What?

05:04.912 --> 05:06.146
Grief, wow.

05:06.181 --> 05:09.149
Um, the inevitability of loss.

05:09.184 --> 05:11.650
Life isn't a straight shot, my friends.

05:11.685 --> 05:14.505
It's full of hills and valleys.

05:14.541 --> 05:16.721
Confront your grief,
your... your fear of it,

05:16.757 --> 05:20.159
and you'll take away its power.

05:21.595 --> 05:23.128
Excuse me, folks.

05:24.031 --> 05:25.297
Can I help you?

05:27.368 --> 05:29.133
Hotel guy is at the door.

05:29.169 --> 05:31.235
He says you haven't paid the bill.

05:31.271 --> 05:33.304
  Tell him pay day is Friday.

05:33.339 --> 05:36.106
You have a job? What do you do?

05:36.142 --> 05:37.308
I cash checks.

05:37.343 --> 05:40.278
Oh, my god. They found that boy.

05:40.313 --> 05:41.145
What boy?

05:41.181 --> 05:43.281
The one that was murdered years ago.

05:43.316 --> 05:44.215
The mayor's kid.

05:44.250 --> 05:46.316
Though a
body was never found,

05:46.351 --> 05:47.417
<i>after an extensive investigation,</i>

05:47.452 --> 05:50.187
<i>the warrens' neighbor
was eventually convicted</i>

05:50.222 --> 05:51.421
<i>for Adam's murder.</i>

05:51.456 --> 05:54.691
<i>But sources say the young
man showed up earlier today</i>

05:54.726 --> 05:56.025
<i>to a downtown police precinct</i>

05:56.061 --> 05:59.996
<i>and clearly identified himself
as the youngest Warren child.</i>

06:00.031 --> 06:03.165
<i>He was promptly taken to
City Memorial for evaluation,</i>

06:03.201 --> 06:06.134
<i>and I am told though his
physical condition is weak</i>

06:06.170 --> 06:09.338
<i>and he has sustained several
injuries of unknown nature,</i>

06:09.373 --> 06:11.139
<i>he is now stable.</i>

06:12.876 --> 06:15.277
Where is he? Where is Adam?

06:15.313 --> 06:17.213
I don't know. She wants us
to talk to the doctors first.

06:17.248 --> 06:18.214
Oh, well, screw her.

06:18.249 --> 06:18.980
I want to see my son.

06:19.016 --> 06:20.682
- Bourbon?
- Shut up. Is Dad here?

06:20.717 --> 06:21.949
Yeah, he's getting a flight.

06:21.984 --> 06:24.051
- Where is she?!
- Right here.

06:24.087 --> 06:25.520
I want to know how something
like this gets leaked.

06:25.555 --> 06:27.355
He walked into a busy precinct, Will.

06:27.390 --> 06:29.224
How? How? Where did he come from?

06:29.259 --> 06:31.326
He said that he traveled
for at least 20 miles.

06:31.361 --> 06:33.361
I've got teams in every woods within 50

06:33.396 --> 06:35.463
searching for the bastard that took him.

06:35.498 --> 06:36.383
Does he know who he is?

06:36.419 --> 06:38.298
- Yes.
- How do we know it's him?

06:38.334 --> 06:40.171
It...

06:40.206 --> 06:42.137
It's been 10 years. He
was supposed to be dead.

06:42.172 --> 06:44.404
We ran a DNA test. It's him.

06:44.440 --> 06:45.572
And is he okay?

06:45.608 --> 06:47.974
I mean, what do the doctors say?

06:48.009 --> 06:50.483
He's got some scars. Signs of abuse.

06:51.380 --> 06:52.446
He was kept in shackles.

06:52.481 --> 06:54.413
He took half the skin off
his hand in the escape.

06:58.085 --> 07:00.085
Oh, god.

07:00.121 --> 07:02.154
Oh, my god. Oh, my god.

07:02.189 --> 07:03.021
All right.

07:03.057 --> 07:05.758
Take a moment, and then shut it down.

07:05.793 --> 07:06.992
Oh. "Shut it down"?

07:07.027 --> 07:08.427
The only thing that's important

07:08.463 --> 07:10.262
is when you walk in
that door, he feels safe.

07:10.297 --> 07:12.364
'Cause I don't know what kind
of hell he's been through,

07:12.399 --> 07:13.231
but it's been a long one.

07:15.869 --> 07:18.403
 Okay.

07:58.276 --> 08:00.408
Hi, Adam.

08:05.416 --> 08:06.948
Hi, Mom.

08:42.884 --> 08:45.284
- Hi.

08:45.320 --> 08:47.821
Hi, my sweet boy.

08:51.326 --> 08:52.591
Welcome home, Ad.

09:07.632 --> 09:13.295
I told him to wait for
me across the street.

09:13.533 --> 09:15.328
You didn't see him
talking to any strangers?

09:15.675 --> 09:16.941
Anyone you didn't recognize?

09:16.978 --> 09:18.734
Ju-just me, the ice cream guy, and Hank.

09:21.697 --> 09:22.877
Who's Hank, Willa?

09:23.110 --> 09:24.510
Just our neighbor.

09:24.545 --> 09:26.345
Right, Mother?

09:27.682 --> 09:29.247
Years ago, there was some sort

09:29.283 --> 09:32.249
of an... indecent-exposure
thing in a park.

09:32.285 --> 09:34.151
"Thing"?! Try conviction!

09:34.187 --> 09:36.053
The man is a sex offender.

09:36.089 --> 09:38.590
The conviction of
my client 10 years ago

09:38.625 --> 09:41.359
was based purely on
circumstantial evidence.

09:41.394 --> 09:44.071
Mr. Asher was bullied
into taking a plea deal

09:44.131 --> 09:45.311
by the police department.

09:45.405 --> 09:47.070
Our city's finest.

09:47.105 --> 09:48.505
So in light of the DNA test

09:48.541 --> 09:50.541
confirming the identity of Adam Warren,

09:50.576 --> 09:52.576
I suspect we can all safely assume

09:52.611 --> 09:54.745
that he wasn't murdered by my client.

09:54.780 --> 09:59.015
I am asking for his immediate
and unconditional release.

09:59.051 --> 10:00.551
Well, I'm going to agree with you,

10:00.586 --> 10:02.781
unless the state has any objections.

10:02.817 --> 10:03.997
 No, Your Honor.

10:04.031 --> 10:04.997
I can go home.

10:05.032 --> 10:06.965
 You can go home.

10:07.001 --> 10:10.635
Mr. Asher, the court
would like to apologize.

10:11.463 --> 10:12.462
 A decade ago,

10:12.497 --> 10:16.432
justice was profoundly
absent from this case.

10:16.468 --> 10:20.369
And therefore, I'd like to
grant you maximum compensation

10:20.405 --> 10:23.271
for wrongful incarceration.

10:23.307 --> 10:26.809
It will be $30,000 a year
for each year that you served.

10:26.844 --> 10:29.678
And with that, the
matter can be adjourned.

10:38.021 --> 10:40.622
Move it back! Thank you very much!

10:40.657 --> 10:42.189
Woman: Mayor Warren!

10:42.225 --> 10:44.692
Mayor Warren! Mayor Warren!

10:47.864 --> 10:50.632
Mayor Warren! Mayor Warren!

10:56.739 --> 10:57.804
Excuse me.

10:57.840 --> 10:59.906
Excuse me. Get out of my way!

10:59.942 --> 11:01.708
- That's my son.

11:01.744 --> 11:03.677
Adam!

11:03.712 --> 11:06.246
Oh, god.

11:06.281 --> 11:07.748
Hey, Dad.

11:07.783 --> 11:10.851
Hi, Chief.

11:14.922 --> 11:16.889
Let's do this inside, John.

11:16.924 --> 11:19.892
  Mayor Warren, are you
happy to have him back home?

11:24.098 --> 11:26.398
  This is a personal family matter.

11:26.433 --> 11:28.900
The mayor will make a statement
when the time is right.

11:28.935 --> 11:30.268
- Thank you.
- All right, vultures.

11:30.303 --> 11:31.870
You got your show. Move it back.

11:31.905 --> 11:34.572
Move it back! Thank you very much!

12:08.085 --> 12:09.585
 I, um...

12:09.974 --> 12:11.941
I took them all down.

12:12.484 --> 12:13.910
The photos of you.

12:13.945 --> 12:15.273
It's just I... I couldn't...

12:15.309 --> 12:16.864
This was so high before.

12:25.989 --> 12:28.289
Do you want to go see your room?

12:29.623 --> 12:31.659
Okay.

12:31.695 --> 12:33.937
We'll just be upstairs.

12:44.721 --> 12:46.807
If we're gonna have a shot at
catching the guy who did this,

12:46.843 --> 12:47.808
I need to question Adam.

12:47.844 --> 12:50.010
It can wait till morning.
The boy just got home.

12:50.046 --> 12:51.578
He knows that Adam's escaped.

12:51.614 --> 12:52.983
He could be on the move.
Every second counts.

12:53.018 --> 12:55.915
I waited 10 years to get my son back.

12:55.951 --> 12:57.516
You can wait one night.

12:57.552 --> 12:59.461
He could have other boys, Claire.

12:59.496 --> 13:01.755
He could be doing
this to other families.

13:07.062 --> 13:09.129
I want the shrink here for this.

13:15.002 --> 13:16.902
You two seem good.

13:19.448 --> 13:20.996
I'm glad you're here.

13:21.021 --> 13:22.289
I came for Adam.

13:31.874 --> 13:33.985
Well, here you go, Hank.

13:34.020 --> 13:36.020
Your aunt Sally and I are real happy

13:36.055 --> 13:38.856
all that ugly business
got straightened out.

13:38.892 --> 13:40.371
Where's my mom?

13:41.013 --> 13:42.138
Oh, boy.

13:45.365 --> 13:47.431
The people there at the facility...

13:47.467 --> 13:49.367
They were supposed to tell you.

13:52.385 --> 13:53.671
She passed, Hank.

13:53.707 --> 13:55.573
'Bout a month ago.

13:55.609 --> 13:58.543
She'd been sick for a long time.

14:01.147 --> 14:02.323
Oh.

14:04.710 --> 14:06.750
Well, they really should have told you.

14:16.028 --> 14:19.194
We were gonna sell the house,
but you can stay for now.

14:22.967 --> 14:24.266
Thank you.

14:25.675 --> 14:28.470
 Tell me about
the man in the woods.

14:28.506 --> 14:29.869
What does he look like?

14:30.269 --> 14:32.057
His skin looks like...

14:32.542 --> 14:34.143
Gravel.

14:34.178 --> 14:36.778
H-he has holes in his face.

14:37.848 --> 14:40.281
What about the place he kept you in?

14:40.316 --> 14:41.883
 Any windows?

14:42.743 --> 14:44.218
Where was the door?

14:44.254 --> 14:46.164
It was up on the ceiling.

14:48.324 --> 14:49.624
Did he ever take you outside?

14:49.660 --> 14:51.325
No.

14:51.361 --> 14:54.094
No. Never? Not... not once?

14:54.129 --> 14:55.596
He came to me.

14:55.631 --> 14:57.631
He always came to me.

15:01.336 --> 15:03.336
<i>Back to our continuing coverage now</i>

15:03.372 --> 15:05.606
<i>of the extraordinary Adam Warren story.</i>

15:05.641 --> 15:07.841
<i>Tonight, Hank Asher... behind bars here</i>

15:07.877 --> 15:10.743
<i>for more than 10 years
for the boy's murder...</i>

15:10.779 --> 15:12.011
<i>Is back at home</i>

15:12.047 --> 15:15.014
<i>after DNA evidence yesterday
confirmed the boy's return.</i>

15:15.050 --> 15:17.684
<i>An emergency hearing
was held this morning,</i>

15:17.719 --> 15:19.686
<i>which declared Asher a free man.</i>

15:19.721 --> 15:21.420
<i>His lawyer tells us tonight</i>

15:21.456 --> 15:24.958
<i>Mr. Asher has no plans to sue
the Red Pines Police Department</i>

15:24.993 --> 15:27.759
<i>despite being wrongly
held for so many years,</i>

15:27.795 --> 15:30.629
<i>which his lawyer calls
extremely generous.</i>

15:30.664 --> 15:34.933
 Sometimes he would forget
to close the door behind him,

15:34.969 --> 15:38.870
and I could see outside
through a window upstairs.

15:38.906 --> 15:41.339
What could you see?

15:42.285 --> 15:43.628
Can I have some more?

15:43.663 --> 15:45.509
Sure, sweetie. In one... one second.

15:45.544 --> 15:46.744
Just... What could you see?

15:48.853 --> 15:50.481
A red dragon.

15:53.013 --> 15:54.380
Okay.

15:55.655 --> 15:56.874
Tell me...

15:56.910 --> 15:59.056
Tell me about that.

15:59.092 --> 16:01.290
The red... red dragon.

16:01.326 --> 16:03.693
I watched it while the
man lied on top of me.

16:03.729 --> 16:05.795
- It was glowing.
- Okay.

16:05.831 --> 16:07.163
It was beautiful.

16:07.198 --> 16:08.564
All right, you can stop this now.

16:08.600 --> 16:10.033
And what was the dragon doing, Adam?

16:10.068 --> 16:11.647
He has been through
enough tonight, Detective.

16:11.682 --> 16:13.440
- We can continue this tomorrow.
- What was the dragon doing, Adam?

16:13.476 --> 16:14.871
The man lied on top of me.

16:14.906 --> 16:16.906
- I said stop this now!
- Every night, he would come...

16:16.942 --> 16:18.140
What was the dragon doing, Adam?

16:18.175 --> 16:19.508
Nina, come on!

16:19.543 --> 16:21.458
He was breathing fire.

16:22.179 --> 16:24.680
Right at me.

16:31.048 --> 16:32.431
Right at me.

16:34.724 --> 16:36.924
I'm gonna get him, okay?

16:40.296 --> 16:42.363
I'm gonna get him.

16:50.097 --> 16:51.881
And why is this all
on me? You're their father!

16:51.962 --> 16:53.295
Danny's drunk!

16:53.331 --> 16:55.815
Willa's becoming a religious nutjob.

16:55.982 --> 16:56.947
Where the hell have you been?

16:56.983 --> 16:58.748
It's not the right
time for a campaign.

16:58.784 --> 16:59.916
Not the right time, not the right time.

16:59.951 --> 17:00.850
When is the right time?

17:00.886 --> 17:02.752
- When he comes back?!
- Don't say... no, no.

17:02.788 --> 17:04.520
- Don't... don't... don't say it!
- He's not coming back!!

17:04.555 --> 17:06.890
Sorry.

17:06.925 --> 17:09.625
I just heard you from back there. I...

17:09.661 --> 17:11.972
The judge denied the
search warrant again.

17:12.066 --> 17:12.680
Oh, great.

17:12.704 --> 17:13.963
Said that there's still
not enough evidence

17:13.997 --> 17:15.792
that Hank Asher had anything
to do with Adam's disappearance.

17:15.829 --> 17:18.191
But... Willa saw them together.

17:18.228 --> 17:19.608
You can't get a search warrant
unless you have evidence,

17:19.631 --> 17:22.369
and you can't get evidence
until you have a search warrant.

17:22.400 --> 17:23.777
Welcome to the justice system.

17:37.857 --> 17:40.789
The low, low price of 10 cents a day,

17:40.821 --> 17:44.452
you, too, could feed a starving child.

17:44.493 --> 17:45.927
Couldn't make it till noon today, champ?

17:52.000 --> 17:53.766
What are you doing?

17:53.802 --> 17:55.936
Ow!

17:55.971 --> 17:57.437
Don't worry. They're still there.

17:57.472 --> 17:58.438
They're like roaches.

17:58.473 --> 18:00.606
While it's lovely to
have you back home again,

18:00.642 --> 18:02.675
could you refrain from
taunting the media?

18:02.711 --> 18:04.344
I still have a job to get back to.

18:04.379 --> 18:05.611
Speaking of which...

18:05.647 --> 18:08.013
I don't think we can stall much longer.

18:08.049 --> 18:10.816
People want to see you
handling this as a mother.

18:10.852 --> 18:12.952
We should book
something... An interview.

18:12.987 --> 18:15.321
This isn't a political
opportunity, Will.

18:15.356 --> 18:16.555
It's our life.

