23:44.899 --> 23:46.132
Holy crap.

23:49.236 --> 23:50.369
A red dragon.

23:50.404 --> 23:53.172
He was breathing fire. Right at me.

26:43.969 --> 26:47.137
It's the sunset hitting
the northern mountain range,

26:47.173 --> 26:48.238
turning it red.

26:48.273 --> 26:51.041
That's our red dragon,
and for it to breathe fire,

26:51.077 --> 26:53.177
oil refinery right behind it.

26:53.212 --> 26:55.145
- So the guy's cabin in the woods...
- Well, from the cabin,

26:55.181 --> 26:58.015
for it to seem like it was
breathing smoke from the head,

26:58.050 --> 27:00.482
it could be anywhere
from here down to here,

27:00.518 --> 27:02.618
and given line of sight on a clear day,

27:02.653 --> 27:04.153
it might go back four miles.

27:04.189 --> 27:07.890
So all deep woods, hardly
populated, perfect cover.

27:07.926 --> 27:09.892
